This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language understanding and classification. It also involves the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in this sub-category. 

It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the development of a neural network-based approach for domain classification. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with the development of intelligent personal digital assistants. 

cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of third-party domains to enhance the capability of IPDAs. 

Finally, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the task of mapping spoken language utterances to natural language understanding domains, which involves retrieving relevant information.
